## Proof-Gated Release Flow

```
Milestone: PENDING
  ↓ (seller signals readiness)
AWAITING_PROOF
  ↓ (seller uploads proof files → stored as R2 URLs in proofSubmitted[])
PROOF_SUBMITTED
  ↓ (buyer reviews)
  ├── APPROVED (buyer accepts)
  │     ↓ (admin triggers payment release)
  │   PAYMENT_RELEASED
  │
  └── REJECTED (buyer rejects with rejectionReason)
        ↓ (seller may resubmit or raise dispute)
      [loop back to AWAITING_PROOF] or [DISPUTED]
```

Proof files are uploaded via the R2 presigned URL flow: client calls `POST /api/uploads/presigned` → receives a time-limited signed URL → uploads directly to R2 → stores the resulting R2 URL in the milestone record. No proof file data passes through the application server.

Payment release is a manual admin action (not automatic) to allow for compliance review before funds move. The admin calls the milestone payment release route after verifying the approval.

---

## Dispute Resolution Flow

Either party can raise a dispute against a specific `Milestone`. The dispute flows through an admin adjudication process.

```
Milestone: PROOF_SUBMITTED
  ↓ (buyer raises dispute)
Milestone.disputed = true, status → DISPUTED
DisputeResolution created → status: RAISED

  ↓ (admin claims the dispute)
UNDER_REVIEW  +  DisputeAssignment record (type: INITIAL)

  ↓ (admin may request more evidence)
AWAITING_EVIDENCE

  ↓ (admin resolves OR escalates)
  ├── RESOLVED
  │     outcome: BUYER_FAVOR | SELLER_FAVOR | PARTIAL_REFUND | SPLIT_DECISION | NO_FAULT
  │     resolvedAt, resolvedBy set
  │     payment consequence applied based on outcome
  │
  └── ESCALATED
        DisputeAssignment record (type: ESCALATION)
        Only SUPER_ADMIN role can resolve escalated disputes
```

### Admin roles in dispute resolution

`AdminRole.DISPUTE_RESOLVER` can claim, investigate, request evidence, and resolve standard disputes. `AdminRole.SUPER_ADMIN` is required to resolve escalated disputes. Role enforcement is checked via `src/lib/admin/permissions.ts` before all admin dispute actions.

### Dispute outcomes

| Outcome | Effect |
|---|---|
| BUYER_FAVOR | Funds returned to buyer |
| SELLER_FAVOR | Funds released to seller |
| PARTIAL_REFUND | Agreed split, buyer receives partial return |
| SPLIT_DECISION | Funds split proportionally |
| NO_FAULT | Funds held pending further resolution |

